Introduction

Hashtag (also stylized as haShtag and #hashtag) was a South Korean girl group under Wannabe Entertainment and LUK Factory. Originally seven, they debuted on October 11, 2017, with the mini album "The Girl Next Door". The group consists of members: Hyunji, Sua, Seungnin, Subin, and Sojin. On March 21, 2023, it was announced that members Aeji and Dajeong would leave the group.

On October 12, 2024, it was announced that HashTag had disbanded due to the expiration of their contracts with LUK Factory.
